<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddd1e7f1e-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s4212"><num value="4212">§ 4212.</num><heading> Protection for declarants</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A declarant under this subchapter shall enjoy the protections of section 3059A(e) <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002387">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002387"><num>1</num> See References in Text note below.</note> of title 18.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddd1e7f1f-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/647/tXXV/s2572">Pub. L. 101–647, title XXV, § 2572</ref>, <date date="1990-11-29">Nov. 29, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/4899">104 Stat. 4899</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="iddd1e7f20-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="iddd1e7f21-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="iddd1e7f22-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">
